{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5faa56f1-b26c-4d02-934b-96b3622513cb","content":"I can help you analyze a .NET crash dump! Here's how to get started:\n\n**First, where is your `.dmp` file?** You can either:\n1. Tell me the path if it's already on this machine, or\n2. Upload/copy it to the current directory.\n\n**Tools I'd use to analyze it:**\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `dotnet-dump analyze` | Managed heap, threads, exceptions, stack traces |\n| `lldb` + SOS | Lower-level native + managed debugging |\n\n**Key commands I'd run inside the dump:**\n\n- `pe` — print last exception (often the crash cause)\n- `clrstack` — managed call stacks\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `syncblk` — deadlock detection\n\nLet me know the file path and I'll start the analysis.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6baacb3e-3242-474a-85b1-a326afafe24f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this. I should check if there are any relevant skills available - looking at the available skills, I see \"dump-collect\" but that's specifically for collecting dumps, not analyzing them. Let me help the user directly.\n\nLet me first check what tools are available and what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":317,"requestId":"980B:343DCA:BFD861:E0F8EE:69F407B8"},"id":"b9097ef3-b52a-4574-8090-f09e01791ddf","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:54:11.463Z","parentId":"5c8a34ae-5d1e-4466-b7b1-d6a912bfd315"}
